      • testLocalTxActorRead

        public void testLocalTxActorRead()
                          throws java.lang.Exception
        Method to test a local Tx actor. The Tx paths are matched to decide if the Tx actor is local or not. This is done by mocking the Tx actor path and the caller paths and ensuring that the paths have the remote-address format Note: Since the default akka provider for test is not a RemoteActorRefProvider, the paths returned for the actors for all the tests are not qualified remote paths. Hence are treated as non-local/remote actors. In short, all tests except few below run for remote actors
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
